quran[33]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,49,"Then what is [the matter] with them that they are, from the reminder, turning away."
  74,50,"As if they were alarmed donkeys."
  74,51,"Fleeing from a lion?"
  77,37,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."
  77,38,"This is the Day of Judgement; We will have assembled you and the former peoples."
  77,39,"So if you have a plan, then plan against Me."
  78,34,"And a full cup.{1}",1:[Of wine which is delicious and does not intoxicate.]
  78,35,"No ill speech will they hear therein or any falsehood -"
  78,36,"[As] reward from your Lord, [a generous] gift [made due by] account,{1}",1:[i.e., as a result of both their own righteous deeds and the limitless generosity of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) . Another meaning is "a gift calculated [to be adequate]."]
  79,28,"He raised its ceiling and proportioned it."
  79,29,"And He darkened its night and extracted its brightness.{1}",1:[i.e., created the day from within the surrounding darkness.]
  79,30,"And after that He spread the earth."
  80,25,"How We poured down water in torrents,"
  80,26,"Then We broke open the earth, splitting [it with sprouts],"
  80,27,"And caused to grow within it grain"
  81,22,"And your companion [i.e., Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) ] is not [at all] mad.{1}",1:[Literally, "possessed by jinn."]
  81,23,"And he has already seen him [i.e., Gabriel] in the clear horizon.{1}",1:[i.e., the eastern horizon, where the sun rises. See footnote to 53:6]
  81,24,"And he [i.e., Muḥammad (ﷺ)] is not a withholder of [knowledge of] the unseen.{1}",1:[Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) did not withhold that knowledge of the unseen which Allāh had revealed to him in the Qur’ān.]
  82,16,"And never therefrom will they be absent."
  82,17,"And what can make you know what is the Day of Recompense?"
  82,18,"Then, what can make you know what is the Day of Recompense?"
  83,13,"When Our verses are recited to him, he says, "
  83,14,"No! Rather, the stain has covered their hearts of that which they were earning.{1}",1:[i.e., their sins.]
  83,15,"No! Indeed, from their Lord, that Day, they will be partitioned.{1}",1:[i.e., they will not be able to see Him.]
  84,10,"But as for he who is given his record behind his back,"
  84,11,"He will cry out for destruction"
  84,12,"And [enter to] burn in a Blaze."
  85,7,"And they, to what they were doing against the believers, were witnesses. {1}",1:[After casting the believers into a trench filled with fire, they sat at its edge, watching them burn to death. This event occurred before the time of Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) .]
  85,8,"And they resented them not except because they believed in Allāh, the Exalted in Might, the Praiseworthy,"
  85,9,"To whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth. And Allāh, over all things, is Witness.{1}",1:[See footnote to 4:79]
  86,1,"By the sky and the night comer"
  86,2,"And what can make you know what is the night comer?"
  86,3,"It is the piercing star{1}",1:[Whose light pierces through the darkness.]
